This paper deals with natural language processing and web-based tasks, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as it deals with natural language processing. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also relevant as the paper deals with finding relevant web elements based on natural language commands. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes models for grounding language in the web environment. cs.HCI (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper deals with user interactions with web elements. Finally, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper proposes and analyzes baseline models for the task.
